<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,151,1005]" pageId="15" pageNumber="292">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,438,654,681]" pageId="15" pageNumber="292">Comparative Notes.</emphasis>
The new species is most similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Becvar &amp; Purchart, 2008" authorityName="Becvar &amp; Purchart" authorityYear="2008" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Hexarhopalus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="292" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eva" subGenus="Leprocaulus">
<emphasis box="[841,999,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="292">Hexarhopalus</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[1016,1155,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="292">Leprocaulus</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[1172,1211,655,680]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="292">eva</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Becvar, S. &amp; Purchart, L." pageId="15" pageNumber="292" pagination="35 - 70" refId="ref10437" refString="Becvar, S. &amp; Purchart, L. (2008) Revision of the genus Hexarhopalus Fairmaire, 1891 (Coleoptera: Tenebrionidae: Cnodaloninae), with description of Malaysphena gen. nov. Annales Zoologici, 58, 35 - 70. https: // doi. org / 10.3161 / 067.058.0102" type="journal article" year="2008">Bečvář &amp; Purchart, 2008</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Pic, 1922)" baseAuthorityName="Pic" baseAuthorityYear="1922" box="[261,823,691,717]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Hexarhopalus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="292" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="difformis" subGenus="Leprocaulus">
<emphasis box="[261,419,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="292">Hexarhopalus</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[435,574,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="292">Leprocaulus</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[590,691,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="292">difformis</emphasis>
(Pic, 1922)
</taxonomicName>
in general appearance. All three species have the same black body, pronotum with strong wrinkles and elytra with regular rows of orderly foveolate punctres. The new species could be separated from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Becvar &amp; Purchart" authorityYear="2008" box="[478,730,763,789]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Hexarhopalus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="292" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eva" subGenus="Leprocaulus">
<emphasis box="[478,636,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="292">Hexarhopalus</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[652,675,763,788]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="292">L.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[691,730,763,788]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="292">eva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the wide and obvious pronotal lateral groove and the lateral groove posteriorly not interrupted; and can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Pic" baseAuthorityYear="1922" box="[893,1078,799,825]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Hexarhopalus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="292" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="difformis" subGenus="Leprocaulus">
<emphasis box="[893,921,799,824]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="292">H.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[937,960,799,824]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="292">L.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[977,1078,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="292">difformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by: 1) the shorter hairs on head and pronotum (1.5 times of diameters of the eye facets in 
<emphasis box="[784,812,835,860]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="292">H.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[826,842,835,860]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="292">L</emphasis>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jiang, Bai, Ren &amp; Wang" authorityYear="2020" box="[864,929,835,861]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Hexarhopalus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="292" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="qiului">
<emphasis box="[864,929,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="292">qiului</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 2 times in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Pic" baseAuthorityYear="1922" box="[1095,1275,835,861]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Hexarhopalus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="292" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="difformis" subGenus="Leprocaulus">
<emphasis box="[1095,1122,835,860]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="292">H.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[1137,1160,835,860]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="292">L.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[1174,1275,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="292">difformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); 2) vanishing median line of pronotum; and 3) shorter aedeagus with wide base (vs. with slender aedeagus).
</paragraph>
